at0098.2.description: *Single word, phrase or brief description that represents the clinical meaning and significance of the laboratory test result. (en)
at0098.2.comment: *For example: 'Severe hepatic impairment', 'Salmonella contamination'. Coding of the diagnosis with a terminology is strongly recommended, where possible. This diagnosis should be aligned with the narrative in the 'Conclusion'. (en)

at0000.1.description: The result, including findings and the laboratory's interpretation, of an investigation performed on specimens collected from an individual or related to that individual.

at0073.1.description: The status of the laboratory test result as a whole.
at0073.1.comment:
The values have been specifically chosen to match those in the HL7 FHIR Diagnostic report, historically derived from HL7v2 practice. Other local codes/terms can be used via the Text 'choice'.

This element is multiple occurrence to cater for the use cases where statuses for different aspects of the result have been split into several elements.

at0075.1.description: The date and/or time that ‘Overall test status’ was issued.

at0068.1.description: A local identifier assigned by the receiving Laboratory Information System (LIS) to track the test process.
at0068.1.comment: This identifier is an internal tracking number assigned by the LIS, and it not intended to be the name of the test.

at0057.1.description: Narrative description of the key findings.
at0057.1.comment: For example: 'Pattern suggests significant renal impairment'. The content of the conclusion will vary, depending on the investigation performed. This conclusion should be aligned with the coded 'Test diagnosis'.

at0098.1.description: Single word, phrase or brief description that represents the clinical meaning and significance of the laboratory test result.
at0098.1.comment: For example: 'Severe hepatic impairment', 'Salmonella contamination'. Coding of the diagnosis with a terminology is strongly recommended, where possible. This diagnosis should be aligned with the narrative in the 'Conclusion'.

at0098.2.description: Single word, phrase or brief description that represents the clinical meaning and significance of the laboratory test result.
at0098.2.comment: For example: 'Severe hepatic impairment', 'Salmonella contamination'. Coding of the diagnosis with a terminology is strongly recommended, where possible. This diagnosis should be aligned with the narrative in the 'Conclusion'.

at0098.2.description: Enkeltord, frase eller kort beskrivelse som representerer den kliniske betydningen og signifikansen av laboratorieresultatet.
at0098.2.comment: For eksempel "Betydelig nedsatt leverfunksjon" eller "Salmonella". Koding med en terminologi foretrekkes, der det er mulig. Diagnosen bør være i overensstemmelse med teksten i "Konklusjon".

at0098.2.description: *Single word, phrase or brief description that represents the clinical meaning and significance of the laboratory test result. (en)
at0098.2.comment: *For example: 'Severe hepatic impairment', 'Salmonella contamination'. Coding of the diagnosis with a terminology is strongly recommended, where possible. This diagnosis should be aligned with the narrative in the 'Conclusion'. (en)

at0098.2.description: Kurze Beschreibung der klinischen Bedeutung und der Aussagekraft des Laborergebnisses.
at0098.2.comment: Zum Beispiel: "Schwere hepatische Beeinträchtigung", "Salmonellenbefall". Die Kodierung der Diagnose mit einer Terminologie, wird nach Möglichkeit dringend empfohlen. Die Diagnose soll zu der Beschreibung im Datenelement "Zusammenfassung" passen.

at0098.2.description: Singola parola, frase o breve descrizione che rappresenta il significato clinico e la significatività del risultato del test di laboratorio.
at0098.2.comment: Per esempio: 'Grave insufficienza epatica', 'Contaminazione da Salmonella'. Si raccomanda vivamente, ove possibile, di codificare la diagnosi con una terminologia. Questa diagnosi dovrebbe essere allineata con la narrazione nella 'Conclusione'.

at0098.2.description: *Single word, phrase or brief description that represents the clinical meaning and significance of the laboratory test result.(en)
Ett enkelt ord, en fras eller en kort beskrivning som representerar den kliniska betydelsen eller konsekvensen av laboratorietestresultatet.
at0098.2.comment: Till exempel: 'Allvarligt nedsatt leverfunktion', 'Salmonella'. Kodning med en terminologi är att föredra där det är möjligt. Diagnosen bör vara i enlighet med texten i "Tolkning av resultat".

at0098.2.description: *Single word, phrase or brief description that represents the clinical meaning and significance of the laboratory test result.(en)
at0098.2.comment: *For example: 'Severe hepatic impairment', 'Salmonella contamination'. Coding of the diagnosis with a terminology is strongly recommended, where possible. This diagnosis should be aligned with the narrative in the 'Conclusion'.(en)

at0015.1.description: The date and time that collection has been ordered to take place or has taken place.
at0015.1.comment: This datetime will be captured primarily in the INSTRUCTION timing, ACTION time or OBSERVATION times. However, as this is a critical piece of information, it can be useful to also associate it directly with the specimen itself.
